Pre-Game Insights: The Botswana men’s football national team, known as the Zebras, will take on Cape Verde in crucial Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) 2025 qualifying matches. The first match is set for October 10, 2024, at 16:00 at the Estadio Nacional Prava Stadium.
Football analyst Jimmy George shared his views on the Zebras’ uphill task, stating that Cape Verde is a quality side and will be keen to face Botswana after their loss to Mauritania.
A key concern for the team is the inactivity of captain Thatayaone Ditlhokwe, who has struggled for playing time at Kaizer Chiefs.
Botswana’s head coach Didier Gomes Da Rosa has named a provisional 25-man squad featuring both local talent and international experience.
